reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I waited about a month before writing this review so I could thoroughly stress test this CPU. I have built computers with various AMD CPUs in the past, and in terms of budget, I have to say this is probably the best there is. I bought it for $100 USD, and in the month I've been using it, I have had zero issues with the product. Under load, the CPU performs extremely well. If you're looking for a good budget CPU, the Ryzen 5500 is the perfect pick

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent Price to Performance Ratio!
reviews.reviewText: This is a great CPU for general use and budget/mid-range gaming! It's able to keep up with all my computing tasks and when gaming with my AMD RX6700XT. Seriously I am very impressed. I will say that when I first installed it, the CPU was running a little warm, but nothing too bad and after a few days it seemed to settle down and now typically sits around 55-65 degrees even while gaming/computing in this hot SoCal summer. I generally see about 20% to 30% usage while playing pretty recent games on 1440p and ultra quality. Would I prefer a 5600x, 5700x or 5800x? Of course, but for the price, nothing beats the value of this CPU and I'm just not willing to spend double the price on relatively limited performance increases. As long as you're not planning to do some extremely CPU-heavy tasks or overclocking, this CPU should fit your needs perfectly. The Wraith Stealth cooler is a nice free add-on as well, although I would suggest if you're looking for ultimate performance, you might want to contemplate a tower air cooler or AIO. However, the Wraith is more than adequate by itself. Anyway, I can't recommend this CPU enough. Keep in mind though, if you're used to Intel CPUs which typically come with integrated graphics, this CPU does not (only G series AMD CPUs like the 5600G for example include integrated graphics although they don't perform as CPUs as well as non G series), so you'll have to buy a graphics card. Also keep in mind X series CPUs like the 5600x are for extreme overclocking (I would go easy on overclocking non-X CPUs and for a lower ranged CPU like this one I would not recommend any overclocking at all). Hope that helps with your decision! Thanks for reading

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It does it's job.
reviews.reviewText: For me CPUs like this, which are budget CPUs are mostly about the price. For $100 USD or less this is an excellent buy. If it's more than that, uhhhh. I'll take the 5600 for $130 Bob.While this is a Zen 3 CPU, it's not PCIe gen4 and you should be aware of this before buying. It's not the same line of CPU that most Zen 3 CPUs which are Vermeer. This is Cezanne. There are 3 Cezanne CPUs, the other two are OEM only, meaning they only come in a PC you buy from a company that makes PCs like Dell, etc........ For the most part this isn't a problem because it's a budget CPU, however if you pair this with something like an AMD Radeon 6500 XT which only uses 4 PCIe lanes to connect to the CPU, you'll get bad performance. So don't do that.Otherwise as long as you pair this with at least an 8 PCIe lane GPU it works fine. You take a tiny hit in GPU performance but not enough to worry about.The bigger hit comes with the NVMe drives, especially in 2023 and going forward. There are now MANY NVMe disks that are a lot faster than 4GB/s, and to give as simple explanation as I can, a PCIe lane is a serial data line. The way a PCIe device/bus works is by grouping a certain amount of lanes so that you get the speed of a single PCIe lane times the number of lanes you have. Any NVMe disk has 4 lanes. It also means the port you plug it into along with what it connects to (CPU, motherboard chipset) has 4 PCIe lanes that it will connect with. So, you get 4 PCIe lanes. So now you need to know the data speed for each lane. For PCIe gen3, the speed of each lane is 1GB/s. For PCIe gen4 the speed of each lane is 2GB/s. So, with this CPU, the best you can get is a data transfer rate of 4GB/s to an NVMe disk. That's it. The newest disks coming out the end of 2022, and 2023 can hit speeds near 9GB/s. Now, most data transfers to/from NVMe disks can't run at that speed. However many disks can run many data transfers faster than 4GB/s, so that means a CPU that runs PCIe gen3 is slowing down modern NVMe disks that can run gen4 or now gen5 speeds. But that's not a statement that has a clear meaning, because just because a disk is called gen4, it doesn't mean most of the data transfers to/from that disk will run at the full bandwidth of PCIe gen4 x4 lanes = 8GB/s. Most gen4 disks rarely hit that speed if ever. Only the most expensive ones do. BUT once again many will run different types of transfers above 4GB/s.So that's the description of what it means to have PCIe gen3 when dealing with modern NVMe disks. You're going to slow down some of the data transfers, not all, depending on how fast (which also means more expensive) the disk is.Yes for a general purpose PC build this is good enough and it's a low cost option that's really good at $100 USD or less. However if the price of this starts to get closer to the Ryzen 5600, I'd rather buy the 5600 because that's PCIe gen4 which is as good as it gets with an AMD AM4 motherboard.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Probably the best budget CPU out there
reviews.reviewText: 6 Core & 12 threads for under $100 probably makes this the best budget CPU right now. You can easily pair this with an older Ryzen board or low end 520m motherboard and get great gaming performance. With that said don’t get confused by the Ryzen SKU numbering, this might be a 5500 but don’t expect it to perform anything like the Ryzen 5600/5600X, this CPU has 1/2 the L3 cache and only supports PCI 3.0. It performance is much closer to a 3600x than a 5600.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Price is right.
reviews.reviewText: System Specs: R5 1600, MSI B550 MB, 32gb 3200mhz RAM running at 2999mhz(system wouldn't post at 3200), RTX 2060 super, 600w EVGA BR Power supply: Cinebench R23- 6136, 3dMark- 7847.Swapped to the R5 5500, and the performance took a tick in the right direction. Same system specs, new cpu, and it's running much smoother, and faster. Now able to run the RAM at 3200, CBr23 score went up to 10389, and 3dM went up to 8400. Much better score all around.For the $99 price tag it's a pretty solid boost to the system. Worth the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excelente por el precio!
reviews.reviewText: Lo compré a 90 usd en descuento y me parece un excelente procesador por el precio, mi motherboard y ssd son pcie 3.0 así que son perfectos para este procesador, la gráfica es una rx 6600 xt que tiene pcie 4.0 pero el rendimiento es excelente incluso sin tener la mayor capacidad posible, lo único es que el chasis al ser mini itx si conlleva a ser más caliente, la gráfica en gaming se mantiene en 60 como máximo y el cpu si sube a 70, no es mucho pero quiero que se mantenga más bajo, la próxima semana le pondré un thermalright ps120 se argb para mejorar la temperatura, y espero que baje unos 15 o 20°. De resto va super bien y no he tenido problema alguno con ningún componente.

Llegó una semana antes de lo que decía, la caja llegó en buenas condiciones, me asusté porque venía en una caja de una PSU vorago jajaja, es un buen CPU para gaming entrada, requiere una gráfica pero con una gráfica decente calidad/precio te corre la mayoría de juegos en gráficos altos o medio altos.
Excellent budget CPU for gaming with 6 cores / 12 threads. Boost to its advertised speed and runs cool with a tower cooler.

reviews.reviewTitle: Produto otimo, de qualidade, porém muita demora pra chegar
reviews.reviewText: Processador maravilhoso, vale muito a pena, tinha um i3 de 4 geração e nem preciso dizer que o computador mudou da agua pro vinho em desempenho. Rodando perfeitamente na placa mãe A520M K V2 que comprei tbm da China, sem precisar atualizar a bios. Porém tenho que ressaltar a demora absurda na entrega do produto, comprei no começo de novembro com prazo de entrega do dia 21 de dezembro ate o dia 5 de janeiro, chegou somente dia 16 de janeiro. O produto ficou preso em curitiba esperando pagamento de taxa mesmo o anuncio dizendo que as taxas ja estariam inclusas, supresa desagradável, tive que por conta propria descobrir ja que nao fui avisado de nenhuma maneira, taxa pequena, entrei em contato com o vendedor ele prontamente fez o reebolso da taxa paga, responde rapido. Comprem mas atentos na demora, muito devido ao pessimo serviço de entregas do nosso pais, e que podera ficar esperando em curitiba o pagamento de uma pequena taxa.

reviews.reviewTitle: 🚀💻 Des performances puissantes avec l'AMD Ryzen 5 5500 et son ventilateur Wraith Stealth! 🌬️🌟
reviews.reviewText: 😊 Globalement, l'AMD Ryzen 5 5500 offre des performances informatiques impressionnantes. La puissance de traitement est vraiment à la hauteur des attentes, et les fonctionnalités multitâches sont fluides.💨 Cependant, je dois avouer que le ventilateur Wraith Stealth fourni m'a laissé un peu sur ma faim. En termes de refroidissement, il fait le travail, mais j'aurais espéré un peu plus de performances, surtout lors de tâches plus gourmandes en ressources.👍 En dépit de mes réserves sur le ventilateur, l'ensemble reste un excellent choix pour ceux qui recherchent une puissance de traitement solide avec un processeur AMD. Il pourrait être intéressant de considérer un système de refroidissement supplémentaire si vous avez des exigences thermiques plus élevées. 💡🔧
Not bad for gaming and other stuff given the price
